venue.fullName: Avron B. Fogelman Arena in the Devlin Fieldhouse

article.headline: St. Louis 76, Tulane 65
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Josh Fisher's 23 points led Saint Louis to a 76-65 victory over Tulane on Saturday night. Fisher shot 6-of-8 from the field and 9-of-10 from the foul line for Saint Louis (15-10, 8-6 Conference USA), which jumped out to a 34-14 halftime lead and cruised from there. Reggie Bryant added 20 points, with nine coming on the foul line, while Izik Ohanon added 13 and Chris Sloan 11. Marcus Kinzer hit three 3-pointers and led Tulane (11-14, 4-10) with 14 points. Vincent Camper added 13 and Chris Moore 11, also hitting three shots from 3-point range. But the Green Wave hit only 31 percent of its shots from the floor, while Saint Louis connected on 48 percent. While Saint Louis only attempted 10 3-pointers, hitting half of them, Tulane threw up 29, making eight. <
